[!INFO] Mnemonics

  • Ketoconazole කන්නද? (The only oral imidazole)
  • Fluconazole - Flu for fluid -> renal elimination
  • Terbinafine for trychophyton (T for T)
  • F-VIP - the triazoles

Mnemonic: VASC (like Vascular)

  1. Antithrombin deficiency
  2. Protein C deficiency - loss of anticoagulant function
  3. protein S deficiency - loss of anticoagulant function


    Longer acting than heparin. Contraindicated in renal failure.
    | Heparin | LMWH |
    | ----------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
    | 15kDa molecule | 4 kDA molecule |
    | | Contraindicated in renal failure |
    | Saturation kinetics at high dose | First order kinetics |
    | | Longer half life |
    | Titrated against APTT | APTT is insensitive; not usually prolonged with LMWH |
    | Given IV (or even sub cut) | Given sub cut |
    | Immediate action when given IV | - |
    | Inactivated by protamine | - |
    | can cause Thrombosis | - |
    | Heparin induced thrombocytopenia | - (lower incidence) |
    | Osteoporosis with chronic treatment | - (lower risk) |


Cerebellopontine angle is bounded laterally by the temporal bone, medially by the brain stem and superiorly by the tentorium.
It contains CN V, CN VII and CN VIII and the Anterior inferior cerebellar artery.
Lesions and defects are given in the image.

  • Toxic dose: 200ml of usual 50% solution.
- Treatment of neurological symptoms with *anticonvulsants*, reducing cerebral oedema, intracranial pressure  etc is the main concern. 
- *Praziquental* and albendazole.

Treatment

  • Of taeniasis - Praziquental.
